{"Title": "Single-Hot-Electron Wave Packets for Quantum Electrical Metrology", "Year": 2018, "Source": "CPEM - Conf. Precis. Electromagn. Meas.", "Volume": null, "Issue": null, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": null, "PageEnd": null, "CitedBy": 0, "DOI": "10.1109/CPEM.2018.8501246", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85057057009&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2018 IEEE.In this paper, we demonstrate an application of non-equilibrium electrons in quantum electrical metrology. Our electrons are emitted from clock-controlled semiconductor single-electron pumps, and are isolated in energy and time from other conduction-band electrons in the system. We show that a voltage comparator can be constructed using these electron wave packets, achieving > 10GHz sampling bandwidth owing to their short (\u223c 10 ps) arrival-time distribution. We also show that investigating the energy and time distribution of the electron wave packets helps to understand the pump operation and improve the current quantisation accuracy.", "AuthorKeywords": ["current standard", "Single-electron devices", "voltage comparator"], "IndexKeywords": ["Arrival-time distributions", "Conduction band electrons", "Electrical metrologies", "Electron wave packet", "Non-equilibrium electrons", "Single-electron devices", "Single-electron pump", "Time distribution"], "DocumentType": "Conference Proceeding", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 2, "EID": "2-s2.0-85057057009", "SubjectAreas": [["Electrical and Electronic Engineering", "ENGI", "2208"], ["Instrumentation", "PHYS", "3105"], ["Atomic and Molecular Physics, and Optics", "PHYS", "3107"], ["Radiation", "PHYS", "3108"]], "AuthorData": {"55707301400": {"Name": "Kataoka M.", "AuthorID": "55707301400", "AffiliationID": "60010785", "AffiliationName": "National Physical Laboratory"}, "6602942484": {"Name": "Giblin S.P.", "AuthorID": "6602942484", "AffiliationID": "60010785", "AffiliationName": "National Physical Laboratory